I'm sorry.
I meant to return your call.

347
00:18:05,751 --> 00:18:07,686
Yes. Yes.
Well, I can appreciate that.

348
00:18:07,753 --> 00:18:10,723
But you must understand that
I was not on duty that night.

349
00:18:10,790 --> 00:18:12,622
In fact,
on the night that it happened,

350
00:18:12,692 --> 00:18:14,320
I was having dinner
with Mr. Andrews

351
00:18:14,393 --> 00:18:16,692
and my area manager, John Bunny.

352
00:18:16,762 --> 00:18:18,663
I suppose after the riot
at Barfield,

353
00:18:18,731 --> 00:18:21,530
the prison must be
in a very disorganized state.

354
00:18:21,601 --> 00:18:24,662
Not that disorganized,
Mr. Soames.

355
00:18:24,737 --> 00:18:26,330
Good.

356
00:18:26,405 --> 00:18:28,169
I was hoping you'd say that.

357
00:18:30,409 --> 00:18:32,435
I'm very confident that the case
will be conclusive

358
00:18:32,511 --> 00:18:36,312
and things will be dealt with
in as short a time as possible.

359
00:18:36,382 --> 00:18:39,113
That said, there is one area
that troubles me.

360
00:18:39,185 --> 00:18:41,984
The defendant, Anthony Kelly,
like all four men is pleading...

361
00:18:42,054 --> 00:18:44,285
Not guilty. Yes.
Yeah.

362
00:18:44,357 --> 00:18:45,689
Have you met Ms. Knatchbull?

363
00:18:45,758 --> 00:18:46,885
No.

364
00:18:46,959 --> 00:18:49,588
But she's obviously had
a lot of visits with Kelly

365
00:18:49,662 --> 00:18:52,655
over the past six months,
and she's seen the cell.

366
00:18:52,732 --> 00:18:54,724
Why did you ask if I'd met her?

367
00:18:55,501 --> 00:18:59,438
Ms. Knatchbull's worried
that her client can be... got at.

368
00:18:59,505 --> 00:19:00,803
I'm sorry?

369
00:19:01,540 --> 00:19:03,236
Well, it's obviously
not meant to sound

